<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="In_popular_culture">In popular culture</span></h2>

<ul>
<li>A bloodhound appears when Big Daddy goes outside while changing the porch light in the 1958 classic film, <i><a href="" title="Cat on a Hot Tin Roof (film)">Cat on a Hot Tin Roof</a></i>.</li>
<li>The bloodhound is seen in the 2009 film, <i><a href="" title="Hotel for Dogs (film)">Hotel for Dogs</a></i>.</li>
<li>A pack of bloodhounds track down Paul Newman&#39;s character in <i><a href="" title="Cool Hand Luke">Cool Hand Luke</a></i>.</li>
<li>A bloodhound is seen while Lennie and Eli are tracking down the title character in the 1991 film, <a href="" title="Bingo (1991 film)">Bingo</a><i>.</i></li>
<li>A bloodhound is seen as part of the dog pack in <i><a href="" title="Secondhand Lions">Secondhand Lions</a>.</i></li>
<li>The bloodhound is seen in <a href="" title="The Borrowers (1997 film)">The Borrowers (1997 film)</a>.</li>
<li>Lightning the bloodhound is seen in <a href="" title="Racing Stripes">Racing Stripes</a>, voiced by <a href="" title="Snoop Dogg">Snoop Dogg</a>.</li>
<li>A pack of bloodhounds search for Tim Robbins character, Andy Dufresne, after he escapes prison in <i><a href="" title="The Shawshank Redemption">The Shawshank Redemption</a>.</i>&#60;ref&#62;<a href="" title="The Shawshank Redemption">The Shawshank Redemption</a>&#60;/ref&#62;</li>
